@adriancole you can use the microseconds component from System.nanoTime().

That microseconds within milliseconds arn't in sync between machines isn't of any great concern. 

You might want to skew it by a fixed amount so the the microseconds component ticks over to zero when System.currentTimeMillis() goes to the next millsecond value.
